1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,440
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

2
00:00:06,440 --> 00:00:08,680
 Good morning.

3
00:00:08,680 --> 00:00:16,000
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

4
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:19,000
 And my wife has always reminded me

5
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:22,520
 after we got married I'd become a better man because of her.

6
00:00:22,520 --> 00:00:29,160
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

7
00:00:29,160 --> 00:00:33,120
 And she has always reminded me how aggressive driver I was.

8
00:00:33,120 --> 00:00:36,800
 But after getting married, I get better because of her.

9
00:00:36,800 --> 00:00:42,280
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

10
00:00:42,280 --> 00:00:46,520
 Before marrying her, I was very low in emotional intelligence.

11
00:00:46,520 --> 00:00:49,920
 But after getting married with her, I increased my--

12
00:00:49,920 --> 00:00:55,840
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

13
00:00:55,840 --> 00:00:58,960
 And she always remind me, do you agree with the change

14
00:00:58,960 --> 00:01:00,880
 that I brought to your life?

15
00:01:00,880 --> 00:01:06,760
 And I have to say yes because of what she has done to me.

16
00:01:06,760 --> 00:01:09,760
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

17
00:01:09,760 --> 00:01:14,520
 And the same way, God has remind us, don't forget his grace.

18
00:01:14,520 --> 00:01:20,440
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

19
00:01:20,440 --> 00:01:28,040
 And you can tell from the Old Testament,

20
00:01:28,040 --> 00:01:31,600
 God has already reminded his people to build memorials,

21
00:01:31,600 --> 00:01:33,520
 to remember his grace.

22
00:01:33,520 --> 00:01:35,800
 And then in the New Testament, always remind us

23
00:01:35,800 --> 00:01:39,000
 what we have enjoyed in Christ Jesus.

24
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:48,800
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

25
00:01:48,800 --> 00:01:56,440
 And now last time, we're talking about Ephesians 1.

26
00:01:56,440 --> 00:02:00,200
 And we were reminded how God has chosen his people,

27
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:02,440
 adopted them as his children, and sealed them

28
00:02:02,440 --> 00:02:03,320
 with the Holy Spirit.

29
00:02:03,320 --> 00:02:06,360
 And now we're in chapter 2 of the book of Ephesians.

30
00:02:06,360 --> 00:02:10,880
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

31
00:02:10,880 --> 00:02:14,320
 This is our passage today, Ephesians 2, 1 to 10.

32
00:02:14,320 --> 00:02:43,120
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

33
00:02:43,120 --> 00:02:45,960
 And this is the first three verses.

34
00:02:45,960 --> 00:02:49,480
 And the outline, it tells us our past.

35
00:02:49,480 --> 00:02:51,120
 We were dead in sin.

36
00:02:51,120 --> 00:02:53,400
 Verses 1 to 3, "As for you, you were

37
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:57,440
 dead in your transgressions and sins in which you used to live

38
00:02:57,440 --> 00:02:59,640
 when you followed the ways of this world

39
00:02:59,640 --> 00:03:02,280
 and the rulers of the kingdom of the air,

40
00:03:02,280 --> 00:03:06,480
 the spirit who is now at work in those who are disobedient.

41
00:03:06,480 --> 00:03:09,480
 All of us also live among them at one time,

42
00:03:09,480 --> 00:03:12,520
 gratifying the cravings of our sinful nature

43
00:03:12,520 --> 00:03:14,200
 and follow his desires and thoughts.

44
00:03:14,200 --> 00:03:19,440
 Like the rest, we were by nature objects of wrath."

45
00:03:19,440 --> 00:03:37,160
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

46
00:03:37,160 --> 00:03:40,880
 And verses 4 to 6, we continue, "But because of his great love

47
00:03:40,880 --> 00:03:44,080
 for us, God, in his rich in mercy,

48
00:03:44,080 --> 00:03:46,920
 made us alive with Christ even when we were dead

49
00:03:46,920 --> 00:03:47,640
 in transgression.

50
00:03:47,640 --> 00:03:49,680
 It is by grace that you have been saved.

51
00:03:49,680 --> 00:03:53,560
 God raised us up with Christ and seated us with him

52
00:03:53,560 --> 00:03:56,920
 in the heavenly realms in Jesus Christ."

53
00:03:56,920 --> 00:04:17,680
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

54
00:04:17,680 --> 00:04:20,880
 Verses 7 to 10, "In order that in the coming ages

55
00:04:20,880 --> 00:04:24,840
 he might show the incomparable riches of his grace

56
00:04:24,840 --> 00:04:27,240
 expressed in the kindness to us in Christ Jesus.

57
00:04:27,240 --> 00:04:31,320
 For it is by grace that you have been saved through faith."

58
00:04:31,320 --> 00:04:33,240
 And this is not from yourselves.

59
00:04:33,240 --> 00:04:36,200
 This is the gift of God, not by works,

60
00:04:36,200 --> 00:04:37,840
 so that no one can boast.

61
00:04:37,840 --> 00:04:41,000
 "For we are God's workmanship created in Christ Jesus

62
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:44,640
 to do good works, which God prepared in advance for us

63
00:04:44,640 --> 00:04:45,480
 to do."

64
00:04:45,480 --> 00:04:51,080
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

65
00:04:51,080 --> 00:04:53,160
 So we start by looking at this passage,

66
00:04:53,160 --> 00:04:54,480
 looking at this picture.

67
00:04:54,480 --> 00:04:57,360
 What can you imagine?

68
00:04:57,360 --> 00:05:01,120
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

69
00:05:01,120 --> 00:05:03,040
 It's this death that we can imagine.

70
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:06,760
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

71
00:05:06,760 --> 00:05:09,480
 So Paul is using this kind of image, this kind of word

72
00:05:09,480 --> 00:05:11,720
 to describe our past.

73
00:05:11,720 --> 00:05:19,360
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

74
00:05:19,360 --> 00:05:22,240
 You see that Paul is not telling us that we were sick

75
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:26,960
 or we were weak, but we were dead in death.

76
00:05:26,960 --> 00:05:29,680
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

77
00:05:29,680 --> 00:05:34,640
 So the state of being dead, it means we are separated from God.

78
00:05:34,640 --> 00:05:43,560
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

79
00:05:43,560 --> 00:05:48,360
 So you go back to Genesis 2, when God tells the humanity,

80
00:05:48,360 --> 00:05:51,520
 don't take the forbidden food.

81
00:05:51,520 --> 00:05:56,920
 Because if you do so, you will certainly die.

82
00:05:56,920 --> 00:06:05,080
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

83
00:06:05,080 --> 00:06:09,840
 And of course, humanity took the forbidden food,

84
00:06:09,840 --> 00:06:11,480
 and we bowed against God.

85
00:06:11,480 --> 00:06:14,560
 And that's why we have death.

86
00:06:14,560 --> 00:06:21,480
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

87
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:24,360
 So he talks about transgression in sin,

88
00:06:24,360 --> 00:06:25,840
 and we were dead in sin.

89
00:06:25,840 --> 00:06:31,360
 It's using the standard of God to evaluate our condition.

90
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:35,880
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

91
00:06:35,880 --> 00:06:39,280
 So you can see men and women, we bow against God,

92
00:06:39,280 --> 00:06:42,640
 and we do not want to respond to God.

93
00:06:42,640 --> 00:06:45,280
 And that's why we are left dead in sin.

94
00:06:45,280 --> 00:06:53,320
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

95
00:06:53,320 --> 00:06:55,760
 So Paul is saying that we were dead in transgression,

96
00:06:55,760 --> 00:06:59,240
 and we were totally dead because there was no way

97
00:06:59,240 --> 00:07:01,480
 we can live again.

98
00:07:01,480 --> 00:07:07,440
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

99
00:07:07,440 --> 00:07:11,200
 So you can imagine, you can see crops in front of you.

100
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:15,000
 And if you yell at it, and you kick it,

101
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:16,800
 and there's no response.

102
00:07:16,800 --> 00:07:27,160
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

103
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:29,720
 So a spiritually dead person cannot respond to God

104
00:07:29,720 --> 00:07:32,800
 and cannot earn his favor, cannot do anything

105
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:36,680
 to invoke change.

106
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:39,120
 We were spiritually dead.

107
00:07:39,120 --> 00:07:59,320
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

108
00:07:59,320 --> 00:08:02,280
 And you can see we are all dead in sin,

109
00:08:02,280 --> 00:08:05,360
 and we cannot do anything.

110
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:08,160
 And verses 2 and 3 describes our conditions.

111
00:08:08,160 --> 00:08:13,680
 "We follow the ways of the world and obey the ruler of the air

112
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:16,360
 and gratify our desires of the flesh.

113
00:08:16,360 --> 00:08:18,680
 And the sinners rule by three powers here--

114
00:08:18,680 --> 00:08:21,480
 world, the devil, and the flesh."

115
00:08:21,480 --> 00:08:28,320
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

116
00:08:28,320 --> 00:08:30,520
 So the world is not talking about our cosmos,

117
00:08:30,520 --> 00:08:31,680
 our physical universe.

118
00:08:31,680 --> 00:08:35,360
 It's talking about a system, a value that hates God.

119
00:08:35,360 --> 00:08:39,400
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

120
00:08:39,400 --> 00:08:44,440
 And behind this world value system is the leader, Satan.

121
00:08:44,440 --> 00:08:51,280
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

122
00:08:51,280 --> 00:08:54,520
 So the devil or Satan is not just--

123
00:08:54,520 --> 00:08:58,440
 it's not what has been described in scary movies.

124
00:08:58,440 --> 00:09:05,160
 It talks about enticing us with his entire worldview.

125
00:09:05,160 --> 00:09:08,680
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

126
00:09:08,680 --> 00:09:11,880
 And the flesh is not talking about our physical body.

127
00:09:11,880 --> 00:09:15,840
 It means our rebellious, sinful nature.

128
00:09:15,840 --> 00:09:21,360
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

129
00:09:21,360 --> 00:09:24,800
 So those who are not born again, who are dead in sin,

130
00:09:24,800 --> 00:09:27,120
 are enslaved by all these three powers.

131
00:09:27,120 --> 00:09:33,200
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

132
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:37,320
 So we cannot blame shift our responsibility to other things.

133
00:09:37,320 --> 00:09:43,080
 We have to see ourselves from the Word of God.

134
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:49,040
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

135
00:09:49,040 --> 00:09:51,360
 And Paul never blames sin entirely

136
00:09:51,360 --> 00:09:54,320
 on Satan or other factors.

137
00:09:54,320 --> 00:09:59,440
 The real culprit is our human self.

138
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:09,040
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

139
00:10:09,040 --> 00:10:11,160
 So this one reminder here is very important,

140
00:10:11,160 --> 00:10:14,680
 that we are dead in sin, and we cannot save ourselves.

141
00:10:14,680 --> 00:10:17,320
 Only by the grace of God, we can live again.

142
00:10:17,320 --> 00:10:32,760
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

143
00:10:32,760 --> 00:10:35,760
 And the second reminder is that when we sin,

144
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:41,880
 we cannot blame our environment and blame to other factors,

145
00:10:41,880 --> 00:10:45,160
 because all of us are sinful.

146
00:10:45,160 --> 00:11:02,240
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

147
00:11:02,240 --> 00:11:05,760
 Well, as you can tell from James chapter 4, 1,

148
00:11:05,760 --> 00:11:09,000
 it says we sin not because of other factors,

149
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:10,440
 not because of the devil.

150
00:11:10,440 --> 00:11:14,800
 We sin because our passions, our sinful nature.

151
00:11:14,800 --> 00:11:31,080
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

152
00:11:31,080 --> 00:11:33,440
 And the world is telling us we sin because

153
00:11:33,440 --> 00:11:34,880
 of the environmental factors.

154
00:11:34,880 --> 00:11:37,280
 And this is the belief of the world system,

155
00:11:37,280 --> 00:11:39,720
 that we sin only because of our environment,

156
00:11:39,720 --> 00:11:41,880
 our biological family, or other factors.

157
00:11:41,880 --> 00:11:44,880
 And one of the examples is in California some years ago.

158
00:11:44,880 --> 00:11:47,400
 Two brothers murdered their parents,

159
00:11:47,400 --> 00:11:49,840
 and they were acquitted because they

160
00:11:49,840 --> 00:11:52,640
 had been abused as children.

161
00:11:52,640 --> 00:11:55,560
 So this decided to try to de-sin them.

162
00:11:55,560 --> 00:11:58,080
 And that is the logic of the world system.

163
00:11:58,080 --> 00:12:09,680
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

164
00:12:09,680 --> 00:12:12,880
 So you can see the logic of the world, the sinful world,

165
00:12:12,880 --> 00:12:16,960
 is telling us robbery because we are poor,

166
00:12:16,960 --> 00:12:20,360
 and we murder because of our trauma in the past,

167
00:12:20,360 --> 00:12:25,520
 sin because of some chemical imbalance inside of us.

168
00:12:25,520 --> 00:12:27,680
 But all of this are lies.

169
00:12:27,680 --> 00:12:43,040
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

170
00:12:43,040 --> 00:12:46,480
 Now you can see from the story of Joseph in the book

171
00:12:46,480 --> 00:12:49,080
 of Genesis, he was betrayed by his brothers,

172
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:50,840
 and he should have become--

173
00:12:50,840 --> 00:12:58,880
 Joseph should have become a very bitter and vengeful person.

174
00:12:58,880 --> 00:13:01,160
 But he forgave the brothers.

175
00:13:01,160 --> 00:13:14,840
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

176
00:13:14,840 --> 00:13:20,280
 And some time ago, we heard the testimony of Mary Joan,

177
00:13:20,280 --> 00:13:23,200
 and she was abandoned by her mother at the age of six.

178
00:13:23,200 --> 00:13:26,200
 And by human logic, she should be

179
00:13:26,200 --> 00:13:29,360
 very resentful against her mother.

180
00:13:29,360 --> 00:13:33,320
 But she became an evangelist, shared the gospel,

181
00:13:33,320 --> 00:13:34,920
 and cared about her mother.

182
00:13:34,920 --> 00:13:36,760
 And that is not environment.

183
00:13:36,760 --> 00:13:39,240
 That is the grace of God transforming her.

184
00:13:39,240 --> 00:13:53,920
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

185
00:13:53,920 --> 00:13:56,720
 So you can see environment or social factors

186
00:13:56,720 --> 00:13:59,000
 is never an excuse for sin.

187
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:02,120
 It may expose our sin or entice us to sin,

188
00:14:02,120 --> 00:14:05,360
 but it cannot cause us to sin.

189
00:14:05,360 --> 00:14:10,120
 God is calling us to respond to pain in our past

190
00:14:10,120 --> 00:14:14,040
 with forgiveness and to face difficulties with faith.

191
00:14:14,040 --> 00:14:21,040
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

192
00:14:21,040 --> 00:14:23,960
 And a side note is that many of the Chinese people

193
00:14:23,960 --> 00:14:26,480
 love fortune-telling and feng shui

194
00:14:26,480 --> 00:14:30,960
 because we try to find the factors for our being

195
00:14:30,960 --> 00:14:33,160
 from the environment.

196
00:14:33,160 --> 00:14:51,520
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

197
00:14:51,520 --> 00:14:57,960
 Yeah, about 1,500 years ago, the great theologian Augustine,

198
00:14:57,960 --> 00:14:59,560
 before he came to Christ, he used

199
00:14:59,560 --> 00:15:04,200
 to be worshiping the false gods and believing in myths.

200
00:15:04,200 --> 00:15:07,520
 But after he came to Christ, he changed.

201
00:15:07,520 --> 00:15:25,160
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

202
00:15:25,160 --> 00:15:30,000
 And Augustine used to believe in some sort of astrology

203
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:33,800
 or cult, and teaching us--

204
00:15:33,800 --> 00:15:36,080
 after he came to Christ, he said--

205
00:15:36,080 --> 00:15:38,040
 he insists that human destiny is not

206
00:15:38,040 --> 00:15:40,880
 determined by stars or astrological factors,

207
00:15:40,880 --> 00:15:43,480
 but by God's will and human responses.

208
00:15:43,480 --> 00:15:52,240
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

209
00:15:52,240 --> 00:15:56,840
 So when God says, who is responsible for our nature?

210
00:15:56,840 --> 00:15:58,840
 Who is responsible for our actions?

211
00:15:58,840 --> 00:15:59,840
 It's not the environment.

212
00:15:59,840 --> 00:16:02,800
 It's not the world, but us.

213
00:16:02,800 --> 00:16:06,160
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

214
00:16:06,160 --> 00:16:26,320
 And the third reminder here is that how Satan works.

215
00:16:26,320 --> 00:16:31,040
 And Satan is trying to deceive us and use values that are

216
00:16:31,040 --> 00:16:34,040
 against God to entice us into sin.

217
00:16:34,040 --> 00:16:42,520
 And Satan is trying to use some evil ideologies

218
00:16:42,520 --> 00:16:45,200
 to entice us to sin against God.

219
00:16:45,200 --> 00:17:00,960
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

220
00:17:00,960 --> 00:17:05,000
 And you can see a lot of modern ideologies--

221
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:10,960
 transgenderism or some other familiar liberal ideologies--

222
00:17:10,960 --> 00:17:14,320
 behind all of this is Satan at work.

223
00:17:14,320 --> 00:17:18,080
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

224
00:17:18,080 --> 00:17:20,480
 And that's why the Bible insists that we

225
00:17:20,480 --> 00:17:21,760
 have to guard our hearts.

226
00:17:21,760 --> 00:17:26,000
 And if we guard our hearts, we guard the rest of our lives.

227
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:30,200
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

228
00:17:30,200 --> 00:17:32,600
 So this passage is telling us we are dead in sin,

229
00:17:32,600 --> 00:17:34,040
 and what can we do about it?

230
00:17:34,040 --> 00:17:37,240
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

231
00:17:37,240 --> 00:17:42,360
 And Paul is trying to tell us there's a U-turn here,

232
00:17:42,360 --> 00:17:46,080
 because, but there is something God has done to all of us.

233
00:17:46,080 --> 00:17:54,480
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

234
00:17:54,480 --> 00:17:58,480
 And Paul is trying to tell us when we were dead in sin,

235
00:17:58,480 --> 00:18:03,280
 but God is working in His grace to turn our lives around.

236
00:18:03,280 --> 00:18:10,160
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

237
00:18:10,160 --> 00:18:13,120
 And we were dead in sin, and God is using His grace

238
00:18:13,120 --> 00:18:16,160
 to turn us around and to give us new life.

239
00:18:16,160 --> 00:18:19,720
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

240
00:18:19,720 --> 00:18:23,080
 See, the essence of being born again or new birth

241
00:18:23,080 --> 00:18:25,760
 is that we can have a new beginning in the Christian

242
00:18:25,760 --> 00:18:26,320
 life.

243
00:18:26,320 --> 00:18:37,240
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

244
00:18:37,240 --> 00:18:40,640
 And many years ago, I was talking to someone in China,

245
00:18:40,640 --> 00:18:43,000
 and we were reading the Gospel of John.

246
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:45,720
 And this person said, being born again

247
00:18:45,720 --> 00:18:49,600
 means only not cursing, not fighting, not smoking

248
00:18:49,600 --> 00:18:50,840
 or drinking.

249
00:18:50,840 --> 00:18:52,160
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

250
00:18:52,160 --> 00:18:53,720
 And this is not rebirth.

251
00:18:53,720 --> 00:19:05,560
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

252
00:19:05,560 --> 00:19:08,000
 See, rebirth in the biblical sense

253
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:10,600
 is not a moral transformation.

254
00:19:10,600 --> 00:19:12,480
 It's not behavioral change.

255
00:19:12,480 --> 00:19:16,120
 It's not our Eastern religion tells us

256
00:19:16,120 --> 00:19:18,040
 there is an awakening in our mind.

257
00:19:18,040 --> 00:19:21,680
 It is what God has done in our lives,

258
00:19:21,680 --> 00:19:23,360
 entirely the will of God.

259
00:19:23,360 --> 00:19:42,760
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

260
00:19:42,760 --> 00:19:45,800
 Just like 2 Corinthians chapter 4 says,

261
00:19:45,800 --> 00:19:50,600
 for God, who said, let light shine out of darkness

262
00:19:50,600 --> 00:19:52,960
 and make this light shine in our hearts.

263
00:19:52,960 --> 00:19:55,080
 So creation is creation out of nothing.

264
00:19:55,080 --> 00:19:58,960
 Just like rebirth in Christ brings us life out of death.

265
00:19:58,960 --> 00:20:01,800
 When God speaks, then the dead will live.

266
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:06,640
 And faith and repentance are the fruit of the work of God.

267
00:20:06,640 --> 00:20:07,920
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

268
00:20:07,920 --> 00:20:31,360
 So you think of the living again story of Lazarus.

269
00:20:31,360 --> 00:20:33,800
 And he had been dead for three days,

270
00:20:33,800 --> 00:20:35,360
 and he was still in the tomb.

271
00:20:35,360 --> 00:20:37,080
 When Jesus came to the door of the tomb,

272
00:20:37,080 --> 00:20:39,520
 he said, Lazarus, come out.

273
00:20:39,520 --> 00:20:43,320
 And Lazarus did not first decide to respond

274
00:20:43,320 --> 00:20:44,640
 to the call of Christ.

275
00:20:44,640 --> 00:20:49,120
 And it was the word of Christ alone that gave him life,

276
00:20:49,120 --> 00:20:50,720
 so that he could respond.

277
00:20:50,720 --> 00:20:53,240
 And that is the mystery of regeneration, new birth.

278
00:20:53,240 --> 00:21:00,000
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

279
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:02,800
 And Paul is trying to tell us God made us alive

280
00:21:02,800 --> 00:21:06,080
 because of all his great love, his God's mercy,

281
00:21:06,080 --> 00:21:08,280
 and his covenant love to all of us.

282
00:21:08,280 --> 00:21:16,680
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

283
00:21:16,680 --> 00:21:19,760
 See, when you see love and mercy and compassion,

284
00:21:19,760 --> 00:21:24,360
 he's talking about covenant promise God has for his people.

285
00:21:24,360 --> 00:21:28,160
 It's not about general human kind of love.

286
00:21:28,160 --> 00:21:36,400
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

287
00:21:36,400 --> 00:21:38,200
 And of course, the Bible tells us

288
00:21:38,200 --> 00:21:41,240
 God loves all the people in the very general sense,

289
00:21:41,240 --> 00:21:44,440
 and sent rain to the just and unjust, the sinful

290
00:21:44,440 --> 00:21:46,520
 and not sinful.

291
00:21:46,520 --> 00:21:55,160
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

292
00:21:55,160 --> 00:21:58,480
 But the Bible insists the redemptive love and mercy

293
00:21:58,480 --> 00:22:02,520
 are given to only those who belong to God's covenant.

294
00:22:02,520 --> 00:22:04,440
 And grace is offered to all of us,

295
00:22:04,440 --> 00:22:07,280
 and effectually given to all the elect.

296
00:22:07,280 --> 00:22:15,920
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

297
00:22:15,920 --> 00:22:18,480
 And thirdly, Paul says we are raised with Christ

298
00:22:18,480 --> 00:22:21,960
 and seated with him in the heavenly realm.

299
00:22:21,960 --> 00:22:28,000
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

300
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:29,920
 And the verse, we are raised in Christ,

301
00:22:29,920 --> 00:22:32,400
 and we are seated in the heavenly realm,

302
00:22:32,400 --> 00:22:34,400
 these are all past tense verbs.

303
00:22:34,400 --> 00:22:35,760
 And it's already done.

304
00:22:35,760 --> 00:22:39,480
 That means Christ is already done for all of us.

305
00:22:39,480 --> 00:22:51,480
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

306
00:22:51,480 --> 00:22:55,200
 And you think about the past tense, the [CHINESE]

307
00:22:55,200 --> 00:22:56,880
 how does it happen?

308
00:22:56,880 --> 00:23:01,240
 How can people still alive on earth already in the past

309
00:23:01,240 --> 00:23:03,960
 seated in heaven and raised with Christ?

310
00:23:03,960 --> 00:23:05,840
 And that's the mystery of being in Christ.

311
00:23:05,840 --> 00:23:15,200
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

312
00:23:15,200 --> 00:23:18,880
 So whenever the Bible tells us that we are in Christ,

313
00:23:18,880 --> 00:23:24,240
 and we enjoy the benefit of being seated in the heavenly

314
00:23:24,240 --> 00:23:28,080
 realm, and we are being saved, they're all in past tense.

315
00:23:28,080 --> 00:23:29,440
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

316
00:23:29,440 --> 00:23:30,640
 And you can think about it.

317
00:23:30,640 --> 00:23:33,480
 Why is it in past tense?

318
00:23:33,480 --> 00:23:40,120
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

319
00:23:40,120 --> 00:23:43,400
 That means in some sense, in the past, we were there,

320
00:23:43,400 --> 00:23:46,880
 and we were buried in Christ, we died in Christ,

321
00:23:46,880 --> 00:23:49,440
 and we were resurrected in Christ.

322
00:23:49,440 --> 00:23:50,480
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

323
00:23:50,480 --> 00:23:50,980
 Why?

324
00:23:50,980 --> 00:24:14,480
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

325
00:24:14,480 --> 00:24:18,080
 That's the mystery of being in union with Christ,

326
00:24:18,080 --> 00:24:20,560
 and what Christ has done in the past.

327
00:24:20,560 --> 00:24:23,520
 His death and his resurrection is a historical event.

328
00:24:23,520 --> 00:24:28,000
 But because of the virtue of being united, union with Christ,

329
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:32,360
 we were, in a very real sense, were transferred from the old

330
00:24:32,360 --> 00:24:33,680
 kingdom to the new kingdom.

331
00:24:33,680 --> 00:24:37,400
 What has happened in the past has already happened to all of us

332
00:24:37,400 --> 00:24:38,440
 in Christ.

333
00:24:38,440 --> 00:24:45,920
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

334
00:24:45,920 --> 00:24:47,640
 And even though we were not there,

335
00:24:47,640 --> 00:24:51,000
 we did not exist back then, but because of the virtue of being

336
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:55,200
 in Christ, what happened to Christ happened to all of us.

337
00:24:55,200 --> 00:24:59,840
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

338
00:24:59,840 --> 00:25:02,920
 So the Holy Spirit is applying what has already happened

339
00:25:02,920 --> 00:25:06,840
 in Christ in the past to all of us.

340
00:25:06,840 --> 00:25:10,440
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

341
00:25:10,440 --> 00:25:11,800
 That's the union in Christ.

342
00:25:11,800 --> 00:25:20,080
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

343
00:25:20,080 --> 00:25:24,760
 And the Bible tells us, because of us being in Christ,

344
00:25:24,760 --> 00:25:27,760
 God has already regenerated us and gave us new birth.

345
00:25:27,760 --> 00:25:29,360
 And we have to ask ourselves, have we

346
00:25:29,360 --> 00:25:32,040
 experienced the new birth?

347
00:25:32,040 --> 00:25:43,600
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

348
00:25:43,600 --> 00:25:46,480
 And it's not because how many times we go to church.

349
00:25:46,480 --> 00:25:50,480
 It's not whether we pray the sinner's prayer or all

350
00:25:50,480 --> 00:25:52,600
 the things that we have done.

351
00:25:52,600 --> 00:25:55,880
 It is whether we have really experienced

352
00:25:55,880 --> 00:25:57,560
 the new birth in Christ.

353
00:25:57,560 --> 00:26:01,840
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

354
00:26:01,840 --> 00:26:04,800
 And when God comes back again, God

355
00:26:04,800 --> 00:26:07,640
 is looking at us, whether you have experienced

356
00:26:07,640 --> 00:26:09,200
 the new birth in Christ.

357
00:26:09,200 --> 00:26:15,720
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

358
00:26:15,720 --> 00:26:16,920
 And you see the truth here.

359
00:26:16,920 --> 00:26:18,840
 It's not because of all of us, we

360
00:26:18,840 --> 00:26:21,560
 can do something to be born again.

361
00:26:21,560 --> 00:26:24,880
 It is Christ taking the initiative

362
00:26:24,880 --> 00:26:27,520
 to grant us the new birth.

363
00:26:27,520 --> 00:26:35,360
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

364
00:26:35,360 --> 00:26:37,480
 You can see the life in Christ.

365
00:26:37,480 --> 00:26:43,200
 We can see our human existence in a very broader perspective.

366
00:26:43,200 --> 00:26:49,320
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

367
00:26:49,320 --> 00:26:50,560
 And life is very short.

368
00:26:50,560 --> 00:26:52,440
 And I think of my son.

369
00:26:52,440 --> 00:26:56,720
 He has already been one year old.

370
00:26:56,720 --> 00:27:08,200
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

371
00:27:08,200 --> 00:27:11,040
 And very quickly, we may die.

372
00:27:11,040 --> 00:27:13,480
 And our life is faded.

373
00:27:13,480 --> 00:27:15,200
 And we will pass away.

374
00:27:15,200 --> 00:27:29,880
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

375
00:27:29,880 --> 00:27:33,840
 But if you see your life in Christ's perspective,

376
00:27:33,840 --> 00:27:37,560
 then our life is not just a few years here.

377
00:27:37,560 --> 00:27:42,240
 And our lives belong to eternity from creation to re-creation.

378
00:27:42,240 --> 00:27:55,080
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

379
00:27:55,080 --> 00:27:57,800
 And Paul is not telling us, OK, what

380
00:27:57,800 --> 00:28:00,760
 we can do as a Christian for Christ.

381
00:28:00,760 --> 00:28:04,880
 He's talking about salvation that we enjoy in Christ Jesus.

382
00:28:04,880 --> 00:28:10,680
 And from eternity to eternity, we enjoy this salvation.

383
00:28:10,680 --> 00:28:15,920
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

384
00:28:15,920 --> 00:28:18,800
 And that is a very objective fact that

385
00:28:18,800 --> 00:28:20,840
 has happened to all of us that in Christ,

386
00:28:20,840 --> 00:28:24,320
 and Christ has done something for us.

387
00:28:24,320 --> 00:28:27,120
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

388
00:28:27,120 --> 00:28:27,880
 Third point.

389
00:28:27,880 --> 00:28:37,760
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

390
00:28:37,760 --> 00:28:40,800
 And the third point is giving glory to God from 7 to 10,

391
00:28:40,800 --> 00:28:42,040
 verses 7 to 10.

392
00:28:42,040 --> 00:28:44,600
 Paul is trying to tell us our salvation is

393
00:28:44,600 --> 00:28:46,960
 by grace through faith.

394
00:28:46,960 --> 00:28:49,960
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

395
00:28:49,960 --> 00:28:51,400
 And you can see the picture here.

396
00:28:51,400 --> 00:28:52,440
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

397
00:28:52,440 --> 00:28:55,160
 And what is he doing?

398
00:28:55,160 --> 00:28:56,560
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

399
00:28:56,560 --> 00:28:57,840
 He's praying.

400
00:28:57,840 --> 00:29:05,320
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

401
00:29:05,320 --> 00:29:11,560
 And you can see he's trying to pray in humility.

402
00:29:11,560 --> 00:29:20,120
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

403
00:29:20,120 --> 00:29:24,520
 And you can tell the empty bowl, if I have pitted on him,

404
00:29:24,520 --> 00:29:27,800
 I put $1 million in the bowl, but the bowl only

405
00:29:27,800 --> 00:29:29,280
 contains $1 million worth.

406
00:29:29,280 --> 00:29:43,000
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

407
00:29:43,000 --> 00:29:46,040
 So the empty bowl does not have any worth in it,

408
00:29:46,040 --> 00:29:52,080
 and only by the giver who gives whatever value into the bowl.

409
00:29:52,080 --> 00:29:56,480
 It's just like us responding to God with faith.

410
00:29:56,480 --> 00:29:58,040
 Our faith has no value.

411
00:29:58,040 --> 00:30:01,760
 And the value comes from what God has given to all of us.

412
00:30:01,760 --> 00:30:05,200
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

413
00:30:05,200 --> 00:30:09,040
 So Paul continues to tell us this is not from ourselves.

414
00:30:09,040 --> 00:30:10,760
 This is the gift of God.

415
00:30:10,760 --> 00:30:16,400
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

416
00:30:16,400 --> 00:30:19,800
 And you can tell it refers not only

417
00:30:19,800 --> 00:30:21,840
 what is whatever given in the bowl,

418
00:30:21,840 --> 00:30:24,400
 but the bowl itself is given by God.

419
00:30:24,400 --> 00:30:27,800
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

420
00:30:27,800 --> 00:30:36,520
 So you can see salvation we have in Christ,

421
00:30:36,520 --> 00:30:38,360
 it's not a trade-off.

422
00:30:38,360 --> 00:30:42,080
 It is because God offers grace, and it's not

423
00:30:42,080 --> 00:30:44,720
 God offers something, that we offer faith.

424
00:30:44,720 --> 00:30:48,480
 Salvation is entirely, entirely the gift of God.

425
00:30:48,480 --> 00:30:52,440
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

426
00:30:52,440 --> 00:30:56,600
 So the gospel, you can tell, it rejects

427
00:30:56,600 --> 00:31:01,280
 any human earning or human favor.

428
00:31:01,280 --> 00:31:08,960
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

429
00:31:08,960 --> 00:31:10,960
 And you can tell in our daily lives,

430
00:31:10,960 --> 00:31:15,720
 we count what we have offered to transaction,

431
00:31:15,720 --> 00:31:19,080
 what we have offered in some sort of exchange.

432
00:31:19,080 --> 00:31:26,520
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

433
00:31:26,520 --> 00:31:28,800
 So our human's general response is

434
00:31:28,800 --> 00:31:31,160
 that we want to offer something and boast about it,

435
00:31:31,160 --> 00:31:35,240
 and because we do something for the transaction.

436
00:31:35,240 --> 00:31:38,360
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

437
00:31:38,360 --> 00:31:43,400
 But the gospel silences all this kind of human boasting.

438
00:31:43,400 --> 00:31:49,040
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

439
00:31:49,040 --> 00:32:01,680
 He said all the religions in the world are basically moralism.

440
00:32:01,680 --> 00:32:04,600
 Good people go to heaven, and bad people go to hell,

441
00:32:04,600 --> 00:32:07,920
 and it's all about transactional exchange.

442
00:32:07,920 --> 00:32:09,880
 We do something, and then we earn something.

443
00:32:09,880 --> 00:32:16,960
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

444
00:32:16,960 --> 00:32:18,360
 But you think about the gospel.

445
00:32:18,360 --> 00:32:20,480
 If we can offer something for God,

446
00:32:20,480 --> 00:32:23,840
 then Christ Jesus does not have to come.

447
00:32:23,840 --> 00:32:29,440
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

448
00:32:29,440 --> 00:32:31,920
 See, that's the uniqueness of Jesus Christ.

449
00:32:31,920 --> 00:32:36,920
 He came, and he died, and he was buried, and he rose again.

450
00:32:36,920 --> 00:32:45,440
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

451
00:32:45,440 --> 00:32:48,280
 And you can tell that's the difference between Jesus

452
00:32:48,280 --> 00:32:54,480
 and all these other religions, including Confucius.

453
00:32:54,480 --> 00:32:59,800
 The Bible tells us Jesus does all of them for all of us.

454
00:32:59,800 --> 00:33:10,920
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

455
00:33:10,920 --> 00:33:14,600
 So many people would accept Jesus

456
00:33:14,600 --> 00:33:17,360
 as a wise teacher and his good teachings,

457
00:33:17,360 --> 00:33:19,520
 but they will reject the cross.

458
00:33:19,520 --> 00:33:23,040
 They will reject the biblical Jesus.

459
00:33:23,040 --> 00:33:34,560
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

460
00:33:34,560 --> 00:33:37,920
 And even we, as Christians, we came to faith,

461
00:33:37,920 --> 00:33:40,920
 and sometimes we work in that kind of mechanism.

462
00:33:40,920 --> 00:33:46,280
 We want to do something that we can earn the favor of God.

463
00:33:46,280 --> 00:33:50,560
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

464
00:33:50,560 --> 00:33:53,520
 See, I love my son because he is my son,

465
00:33:53,520 --> 00:33:57,680
 and there's kind of an exchange or transactional thing

466
00:33:57,680 --> 00:33:58,440
 going on.

467
00:33:58,440 --> 00:34:09,200
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

468
00:34:09,200 --> 00:34:12,320
 You see, I love my son because the virtue of the fact

469
00:34:12,320 --> 00:34:15,440
 that he is my son, not because he does something good

470
00:34:15,440 --> 00:34:16,720
 or he does something bad.

471
00:34:16,720 --> 00:34:18,160
 Because he is my son.

472
00:34:18,160 --> 00:34:19,040
 That's the identity.

473
00:34:19,040 --> 00:34:20,880
 That's why I love him.

474
00:34:20,880 --> 00:34:28,160
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

475
00:34:28,160 --> 00:34:31,760
 And if he grow up and becomes bigger and older,

476
00:34:31,760 --> 00:34:36,320
 and he, my son, wants to do something and earn my favor.

477
00:34:36,320 --> 00:34:41,480
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

478
00:34:41,480 --> 00:34:44,560
 And then the son will tell me, no, I

479
00:34:44,560 --> 00:34:47,600
 have done something for you, so many things for you,

480
00:34:47,600 --> 00:34:49,040
 to treat you as my father.

481
00:34:49,040 --> 00:34:50,600
 Can you love me more?

482
00:34:50,600 --> 00:34:52,320
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

483
00:34:52,320 --> 00:34:54,120
 And then I would be so confused.

484
00:34:54,120 --> 00:35:00,440
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

485
00:35:00,440 --> 00:35:02,920
 Because he does not understand my love for him.

486
00:35:02,920 --> 00:35:07,920
 It's not a condition on what he has done and what he is.

487
00:35:07,920 --> 00:35:14,680
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

488
00:35:14,680 --> 00:35:18,760
 You see, if he wants to earn my favor by doing good things,

489
00:35:18,760 --> 00:35:23,400
 he does not know the basis of my love.

490
00:35:23,400 --> 00:35:28,600
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

491
00:35:28,600 --> 00:35:31,320
 See, in much the same way, our relationship with God

492
00:35:31,320 --> 00:35:36,800
 is the same, because of his unconditional love for all of us.

493
00:35:36,800 --> 00:35:50,960
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

494
00:35:50,960 --> 00:35:53,120
 See, God's gracious love for all of us

495
00:35:53,120 --> 00:35:56,040
 is not because of what we have done or good things we have done

496
00:35:56,040 --> 00:35:58,760
 for him to earn his favor.

497
00:35:58,760 --> 00:36:01,960
 It's all because we are all in Christ.

498
00:36:01,960 --> 00:36:04,000
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

499
00:36:04,000 --> 00:36:07,040
 So the emphasis is that we are in Christ.

500
00:36:07,040 --> 00:36:23,160
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

501
00:36:23,160 --> 00:36:24,840
 And then Paul continues to tell us

502
00:36:24,840 --> 00:36:28,360
 the purpose of salvation is that we

503
00:36:28,360 --> 00:36:30,440
 will be able to do spiritual good works,

504
00:36:30,440 --> 00:36:35,560
 and the spiritual good works is not human moral practice.

505
00:36:35,560 --> 00:36:40,720
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

506
00:36:40,720 --> 00:36:43,360
 And then it tells us we can show the grace

507
00:36:43,360 --> 00:36:44,840
 to all the generations.

508
00:36:44,840 --> 00:36:55,600
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

509
00:36:55,600 --> 00:36:57,760
 You see that because we are saved in Christ,

510
00:36:57,760 --> 00:37:00,520
 so that our lives can be used by God

511
00:37:00,520 --> 00:37:05,840
 to show forth his grace and his kindness in our lives.

512
00:37:05,840 --> 00:37:14,600
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

513
00:37:14,600 --> 00:37:16,160
 So you can see the plan of salvation

514
00:37:16,160 --> 00:37:19,360
 is not just to save us from sin or from death,

515
00:37:19,360 --> 00:37:23,600
 but to save us so that we can glorify God.

516
00:37:23,600 --> 00:37:36,360
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

517
00:37:36,360 --> 00:37:38,040
 And the quotes here are very meaningful,

518
00:37:38,040 --> 00:37:39,920
 and I want to quote it.

519
00:37:39,920 --> 00:37:43,960
 "Jesus Christ died for sinners, but more for God himself.

520
00:37:43,960 --> 00:37:47,760
 And God put forth as appropriate agent by his blood

521
00:37:47,760 --> 00:37:49,400
 to be received by faith, and this

522
00:37:49,400 --> 00:37:51,400
 is the show of the glory of God."

523
00:37:51,400 --> 00:38:01,640
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

524
00:38:01,640 --> 00:38:05,520
 So you can see we are being saved in Christ

525
00:38:05,520 --> 00:38:10,000
 so that our lives can show the righteousness of God.

526
00:38:10,000 --> 00:38:21,800
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

527
00:38:21,800 --> 00:38:26,000
 So you can see in the entire biblical history, what

528
00:38:26,000 --> 00:38:31,080
 God has done in Christ, what Jesus has done in history,

529
00:38:31,080 --> 00:38:35,960
 whether we understand or comprehend it exhaustively,

530
00:38:35,960 --> 00:38:38,880
 it is all for the purpose of God.

531
00:38:38,880 --> 00:38:50,560
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

532
00:38:50,560 --> 00:38:54,120
 So the application point for us is that salvation is by grace,

533
00:38:54,120 --> 00:38:56,000
 is not by our human work.

534
00:38:56,000 --> 00:38:58,880
 When we face failures or struggles or guilt,

535
00:38:58,880 --> 00:39:02,560
 we need to return to the grace of God, not our self-effort.

536
00:39:02,560 --> 00:39:14,280
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

537
00:39:14,280 --> 00:39:18,280
 And you can see whatever God has done for all of us

538
00:39:18,280 --> 00:39:20,760
 is ultimately for his glory.

539
00:39:20,760 --> 00:39:23,120
 And we have to ask the question whether we

540
00:39:23,120 --> 00:39:27,280
 live in such a way that would bring God glory.

541
00:39:27,280 --> 00:39:29,800
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

542
00:39:29,800 --> 00:39:32,200
 Just like this verse says, whether you eat or drink,

543
00:39:32,200 --> 00:39:37,840
 you live so that you can bring glory to God.

544
00:39:37,840 --> 00:39:42,880
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

545
00:39:42,880 --> 00:39:47,600
 So whatever we have done or Christ has done in our lives,

546
00:39:47,600 --> 00:39:48,960
 of eternal value.

547
00:39:48,960 --> 00:39:56,000
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

548
00:39:56,000 --> 00:40:16,000
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

549
00:40:16,000 --> 00:40:19,400
 So we can see there's no division whether someone

550
00:40:19,400 --> 00:40:22,400
 is preaching so it's more valuable to God,

551
00:40:22,400 --> 00:40:25,960
 or we eat or drink, or we conduct our daily life,

552
00:40:25,960 --> 00:40:28,120
 and that is less value.

553
00:40:28,120 --> 00:40:30,760
 Everything, everything, whatever we do,

554
00:40:30,760 --> 00:40:33,720
 whatever we think, is for the glory of God.

555
00:40:33,720 --> 00:40:35,440
 Everything is holy and sacred.

556
00:40:35,440 --> 00:40:40,280
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

557
00:40:40,280 --> 00:40:44,760
 So there's no sacred or worldly division in Christ.

558
00:40:44,760 --> 00:40:50,760
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

559
00:40:50,760 --> 00:40:52,560
 See, the emphasis is that whatever

560
00:40:52,560 --> 00:40:57,800
 we do in Christ, whatever we do for Christ,

561
00:40:57,800 --> 00:40:59,800
 it has eternal value.

562
00:40:59,800 --> 00:41:08,520
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

563
00:41:08,520 --> 00:41:10,880
 So when God sees what you do, it's

564
00:41:10,880 --> 00:41:14,320
 not because the intrinsic value of your doing.

565
00:41:14,320 --> 00:41:18,120
 It is because what you do in Christ.

566
00:41:18,120 --> 00:41:27,280
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

567
00:41:27,280 --> 00:41:29,200
 So it's not talking about glorifying God,

568
00:41:29,200 --> 00:41:32,640
 we have to do something grand or do something big.

569
00:41:32,640 --> 00:41:36,280
 It's talking about faithful daily living in Christ,

570
00:41:36,280 --> 00:41:36,880
 for Christ.

571
00:41:36,880 --> 00:41:42,680
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

572
00:41:42,680 --> 00:41:46,160
 And this is the end of message, and let's pray together.

573
00:41:46,160 --> 00:41:54,120
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

574
00:41:54,120 --> 00:41:55,600
 Heavenly Father, we give you thanks

575
00:41:55,600 --> 00:41:58,320
 because you have raised us from death to life

576
00:41:58,320 --> 00:42:00,480
 and give us new heart and new life.

577
00:42:00,480 --> 00:42:07,920
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

578
00:42:07,920 --> 00:42:11,120
 And if there is any one of us among us

579
00:42:11,120 --> 00:42:14,960
 who has not been experienced the rebirth or born again,

580
00:42:14,960 --> 00:42:17,160
 and God, we pray that you will bring us

581
00:42:17,160 --> 00:42:19,040
 new life by your Spirit.

582
00:42:19,040 --> 00:42:36,240
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

583
00:42:36,240 --> 00:42:38,400
 And for all of us who are already in Christ,

584
00:42:38,400 --> 00:42:43,280
 and help us to know that our lives are not small or not

585
00:42:43,280 --> 00:42:46,600
 valuable, but we are in Christ and we are not

586
00:42:46,600 --> 00:42:47,720
 separated from you.

587
00:42:47,720 --> 00:42:50,200
 Whatever we do, do it for your glory.

588
00:42:50,200 --> 00:42:52,640
 [SPEAKING CHINESE]

589
00:42:52,640 --> 00:42:55,520
 In Jesus' name we pray, amen.

590
00:42:55,520 --> 00:42:56,160
 Thank you, Paul.

591
00:42:56,160 --> 00:42:56,660
 Thank you.

